The paper deals with property testing of functions on a finite field, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of Gowers norms and polynomials suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and algebraic coding theory (cs.DS). The paper also involves the study of subspaces and low-rank structures, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
